stnTemporary.name: stnTemporary
stnTemporary.description: stnTemporary provides a root object identifier from which temporary mibs may be based. MIBs are typicially based here if they fall in one of two categories: 1) are IETF work-in-process mibs which have not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the IANA. 2) are stn work-in-process which has not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the stn assigned number authority, typicially because the mib is not ready for deployment. NOTE WELL: support for mibs in the stnTemporary subtree will be deleted when a permanent object identifier assignment is made.

stnMibModules.name: stnMibModules
stnMibModules.description: stnModules provides a root object identifier from which MODULE-IDENTITY values may be assigned.
